description.narrative: In response to Covid-19 emergency, the proposed project development objective is to support critical food supply chains and create short-term economic opportunities.

condition.narrative: FA Schedule 2 Section 1.A.2(a): through MOF, establish by not later than two (2) months after the Effective Date, and thereaftermaintain throughout the period of implementation of the Project, the Project Steering Committee for the overall guidance andstrategic orientation for the Project, with mandate, composition, and membership as set forth in detail in the Project OperationsManual.

FA Schedule 2 Section 1.A.2(c): through MAIL develop and adopt, by not later than four months prior to the Closing Date, asustainability plan, in a manner satisfactory to the Association, setting forth detailed requirements for the sustainability ofactivities supported under the Project.

FA Schedule 2 Section 1.B.1(a): The Recipient shall through MAIL adopt, by not later than one month after the Effective Date, andthereafter implement the Project in accordance with the provisions of, the Project Operations Manual.

FA Schedule 2 Section 1.E.1(a): The Recipient shall through MAIL prepare and adopt by not later than October 21st of each year, anannual work plan and budget (the “Annual Work Plan and Budget”) for the following fiscal year in a manner, form and substancesatisfactory to the Association.

FA Schedule 2 Section 1.E.1(a): The Recipient shall through MAIL prepare and adopt the first Annual Work Plan and Budget for thefirst year of Project implementation by not later than two (2) months after the Effective Date.
